# Movie Server deploy workflow

When the user asks for a code change, always complete all three deploy targets before finishing:

1. **Local Docker** — rebuild and restart: `docker compose up --build -d`
2. **Home Assistant** — bump `movie-server/config.yaml`, `movie-server/Dockerfile` (`APP_BUILD_VERSION`), `movie-server/CHANGELOG.md`, `src/movie_server/package.json`, and `custom_components/movie_server/manifest.json`; then commit and push (do not ask first).
3. **Tizen TV** — bump `tizen-hello-test/HelloTV/config.xml` version and sync any shared UI/API changes into `tizen-hello-test/HelloTV/`

Do not leave server-only changes unported to the Tizen bundled UI when the dashboard behavior changed.

Fix `docker-compose.yml` port mapping if needed so host `${PORT}` maps to the same container port the app listens on.
